      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I've written a few automated tests that test the GUI interface. https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/qt/test/wallettests.cpp sends a transaction with the send coins dialog, looks up the transaction in the transaction view, starts a fee bump, and confirms it. \r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/qt/test/apptests.cpp runs a command on the RPC console and checks the HTML output.\r\n\r\nThe tests run in the background by default, but you can run them interactively and see the GUI windows using the `test_bitcoin-qt -platform xcb` option.\r\n\r\nI'm also planning on writing a new test in #15936 that will test editing and loading the GUI's pruning and proxy settings.",
