      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "Looking a little more closely, wallettests.cpp is not really a great place to test listing wallets since it currently only tests creating individual application dialogs instead of the whole application window. I think [`AppTests::guiTests`](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/e2182b02b5af13f0de38cf8b08bb81723387c570/src/qt/test/apptests.cpp#L85) would be a better place to add a wallet listing & loading test. It could start by opening the `m_open_wallet_action` menu, similar to how the existing code triggers the [`openRPCConsoleAction`](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/e2182b02b5af13f0de38cf8b08bb81723387c570/src/qt/test/apptests.cpp#L88-L91) action.",
